Well here's an update for the masses:

                Life's been a bitch and i've been bored out of my mind. I haven't found anyone cool to hang out with at school. I know people but they're same as the people at St.F . I hate not having friends, before I didn't think it would be that big of a deal not to have friends but now I know what all those kids without friends feel like but it feels like even they have friends. I haven't even seen anyone remotely pretty at my school they are a bunch of "pansy valley girls" as tanisnikana would say. I bet she is laughing at me, fucking bitch. UGH why can't i find some cool people to play World of Warcraft with or just someone to exchange manga with?! School has pretty much taken over my life and this winter break has been great and has given me a breather for a bit, but in a while school will start again and i'll have to bust my ass to get an A in chemistry just like last semester. I'd rather be living with my dad but i'm mom won't let me and i'm going to turn another age again soon. Not to vague is it? Good.

Bye all

True Story. A religion teacher assigned her class an essay on what makes a good Christian. One student wrote about praying nightly, say no to abortion, banning gay marriage, and donating money. The other student wrote about talking to God and allowing people to enjoy their lives, and supporting gay marriage. The day the teacher was to hand the papers back, she called up the second student and told him she would pray for him when he went to hell. The student asked why would he be going to hell, and why he got an F on his paper. The teacher told him that Catholisim is against gay marriage. The student looked at her for a minute, then said aloud, "I'm gay." The teacher kicked him out of class as if he had said fuck or worshipped Satan. A girl in the back of class who had a boyfriend and was obviously straight got up and left too.

If you would leave the classroom, repost this. It doesn't matter if you're straight, bi, or gay. It doesn't matter if you're Catholic or not. Everyone is a human being and deserves happiness.
